messages.content: concentration is probably a better version of this

really good for a common relic. This makes all of your RNG cards far better by just removing part of the RNG. Its effects on a run are far reaching, for example. Tailwhip becomes uppercut, snake rake always draws a card, snake sap is a better seing red and restock draws +1 card. Those 4 cards are all good cards that you are using on a regular basis, so this relic gets significant value in almost every run its seen. This wont fix all rng cards, like glittering gambit is not going to be made fantastic by gaining +1 gold. But just hitting those 4 is good.
tbh I will admit, this relic is kinda solving a problem that really shouldn't have existed in the first place
in griftlands random damage numbers are safer because concentration is much much easier to get
Most of snecko's RNG cards are really strong independent of their luck attached.
restock is a better scrawl in the context of its character. Having uppercut in the starter deck would be insanely busted if there was not that RNG attached.

unless i'm miscounting snecko has 10 cards that do this; 6 of those cards are good (tail whip, snake rake, restock, snake sap, rain of dice, glittering gambit). The bad ones being dice crush, boulder and block plus iron fang (all 4 cards that would be bad even if they had no luck attached to them at all)
<dice boulder> in particular is one of the cards of all time

It has some strong interactions with cards with small ranges like snake sap, tail whip, and snake rake, but is not very helpful for the cards with larger ranges. Sadly, those cards (dice block, iron fang, dice crush, dice boulder) need the help a lot more, and so I find that this relic is usually doesn't change very much about how you evaluate sneckos card pool. Most of the range cards are rather frustrating and understatted anyways, and I don't recommend taking them regardless of what's happening in the run. Making your starting tail whip quite a bit more consistent is a very nice upside, so this is usually worth buying at a shop if you see it (and still have a relatively small deck), especially if you have a copy of snake sap or snake rake as well.
